Stage 1 Preparation

Goal

Set up the hunt by defining what suspicious behavior needed to be investigated.

Hunt Objective

The objective was to determine whether internal network slowdowns were caused by suspicious activity from a device inside the network.

The investigation focused on identifying excessive failed network connections, possible port scanning behavior, and any process activity that could explain the connection pattern.

Hypothesis

```text
If a device inside the internal network was causing sudden network slowdowns, then Microsoft Defender for Endpoint telemetry may show excessive failed connection attempts, sequential port activity, or suspicious process execution such as PowerShell launching a port scanning script.
```

Risk Factors

| Risk Factor | Why It Matters |
|---|---|
| Internal traffic allowed by default | Devices may be able to communicate broadly across the network |
| Unrestricted PowerShell usage | Scripts can be used to automate scanning or discovery |
| Older devices on the network | Older systems may be more sensitive to connection floods or scanning |
| No clear internal traffic restrictions | Makes lateral discovery easier |
| Administrative account usage | Suspicious activity under an admin account increases risk |
| Sequential failed connections | May indicate port scanning behavior |

